(This review is dedicated to those coming back to the game after a long break like I have taken.) I honestly feel like it's been a downgrade since the last time I have played clash. I picked up the game after 3 years and I feel that the game as a whole is sincerely divided. Main issue: Clans have become so over-saturated with clan xp (experience) since the last time I have joined and it just seems pointless to invest creating a new clan (which is what I want) since it's difficult to compete with the now higher townhalls recruiting. Sub issues: -Majority of people on the English speaking server don't even speak the language good enough to understand or not. -It's often found that many 'noise-makers' inhibit the global chat. These people start arguments about anything from base design to racism. People are genuinely bored and resort to this. Many good players reside in their clan and don't communicate in global chat or never join clans at all. -The good clans which are almost family oriented are too demanding and not diverse enough for myself as a player. My only issue not being active enough for their clans, which is absurd. I spend enough time on the game everyday as is.
